  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dd4 \u0dbd\u0dd6\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0d9c\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dab\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da9\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A message from the big onion farmer to the minister",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The local big onion farmers in the districts of Anuradhapura, Matale, Polonnaruwa have requested the Minister of Agriculture to give some amount of that fertilizer to the local big onion farmer and arrange some program to buy ground oil during the distribution of the chemical fertilizers that have been ordered from foreign countries.",
        "At a time when local big onion cultivation has been completely abandoned, the local big onion farmers have entered into onion cultivation to some extent due to their trust in the government.",
        "Accordingly, farmers have started planting a significant amount of local large onion plants in Anuradhapura, Matale and Polonnaruwa district these days.",
        "Pointing out that due to the production of local big onions, the farmers will save a lot of dollars flowing from the country to foreign countries. They said that since farming is their job, they cannot lose it, so they should immediately give some amount of the chemical fertilizers brought to the country for the next replanting to the local big onion cultivation, which is very small. That giving should be done.",
        "Also, if some reasonable arrangements are made to get large onions from kerosene or diesel fuel stations to provide water which is essential for onion cultivation, the local large onion harvest can be done after these three and a half months.",
        "The farmers have informed the Minister of Agriculture that then the dollar reserves in this country will stop flowing to foreign countries for big salt and they will be able to provide food to the people for many months with local big onions."
      ],
